# /etc/pam.d/tessera — opt-in МКЦ activation stack.
#
# This is NOT the PAM stack that authenticates end users — that lives
# at /etc/pam.d/tessera (and -optional / -only variants). This stack
# is loaded by systemd because the `mac-integrity.conf.example`
# drop-in declares `PAMName=tessera`. When the daemon is forked,
# systemd opens a PAM session against this stack so the parsec session
# modules can apply caps + ilevel from capdb/micdb to the daemon
# process.
#
# Activation (full walkthrough: docs/install.md §«МКЦ — опциональная
# активация»):
#
#     sudo install -m 0644 \
#         /usr/share/tessera/pam.d/tessera.example \
#         /etc/pam.d/tessera
#
# Prerequisites on Astra SE strict-mode:
#   - /etc/parsec/capdb/<uid-of-tessera> must include PARSEC_CAP_CHMAC
#     (bit 3): `sudo /sbin/usercaps -m "+3" tessera`.
#   - /etc/parsec/micdb/<uid-of-tessera> must declare ilevel=63
#     (otherwise the daemon will not be able to relabel high-ilevel
#     state files): `sudo /sbin/pdpl-user --ilevel 63 tessera`.
#
# Why session-only:
#   - auth/account phases are not meaningful for a service account
#     started by systemd; we short-circuit them with pam_permit.so so
#     PAM does not block service start.
#   - The two parsec session modules are the actual workhorses: they
#     read /etc/parsec/capdb and /etc/parsec/micdb keyed by the running
#     uid (tessera) and apply the resulting caps + ilevel to the
#     daemon process before ExecStart fires.

auth       required   pam_permit.so
account    required   pam_permit.so

session    required   pam_parsec_cap.so
session    required   pam_parsec_mac.so
